                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290115-241-victim1845 t18290115-241-viclabel1295"></join>, and live in Russell-court. At a quarter past four o'clock, last Thursday, I saw the prisoner take this book; I followed her, about a dozen yards, and took it from her - she said she merely took it for a lark; there was another woman with her.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had not got a yard from the door, and asked if he had got a Vesper book; he said I did not know how to read one, and for my impudence he would give me in charge.</p>

